## Design guardrails

- Keep implementation inside `libs/sdk-dsl`
- Keep runtime package boundary clean; `document-processor` is test-only
- Use only public imports from `@blue-labs/language` and `@blue-labs/document-processor`
- Do not import from internal `src/...` paths across libraries
- Build Stage 4 as a composition layer on top of Stage 1–3 primitives when practical
- Prefer thin, explicit wrappers over hidden magic
- Keep the public API close to Java unless TypeScript/runtime constraints require a deviation

## Behavioral guardrails

- Access-related builders must produce runtime-correct MyOS permission request/control flows aligned to the final mapping reference
- Linked-access builders must align to anchors/links plus linked-doc permission request/control shapes
- Agency builders must align to worker-agency permission request/control and worker-session start request shapes
- Do not silently force root document `type` unless Java plus mapping reference clearly require it
- Do not duplicate inherited admin contracts on documents already typed as `MyOS/MyOS Admin Base` unless explicitly requested
- Preserve deterministic key generation and contract insertion order

## Completion

Do not claim completion unless verification commands were run and reported.
